A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO LAW ENFORCEMENT.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the State is
2 coiranitted to ensuring that all Hawaii residents are treated
3 equally notwithstanding race, religion, national origin,
4 disability status, sexual orientation, gender, or immigration
5 status.
6 The legislature further finds that all Hawaii residents are •
7 entitled to live in dignity and without fear. The legislature
8 also finds that immigrants are valuable and essential members of
9 the community and should be able to live full and productive
10 lives without fear of the government.
11 Furthermore, the legislature finds that a relationship of
12 trust between the State's immigrant community and state and
13 county agencies is central to the public safety of the people of
14 Hawaii. This trust is threatened when state and county agencies
15 are entangled with federal immigration enforcement, with the
16 result that immigrant community members fear going to court.
2026-2570 SB2057 CDl SMA.docx
