1 seeking basic health or other services, or pursuing education to
2 the detriment of public safety and the well-being of all
3 residents.
4 Therefore, the purpose of this Act is to prohibit:
5 (1) Any state or county law enforcement agency or law
6 enforcement official from entering into an agreement
7 under title 8 United States Code section 1357(g) or
8 any other federal law that permits state or county
9 agencies to engage in immigration enforcement; and
10 (2) State and county law enforcement agencies and law
11 enforcement officials from engaging in certain
12 immigration-related actions, except under limited
13 circumstances.
14 SECTION 2. The Hawaii Revised Statutes is amended by
15 adding a new chapter to be appropriately designated and to read
16 as follows:
17 "CHAPTER
18 IMMIGRATION ENFORCEMENT; PROHIBITIONS
19 § -1 Definitions. As used in this chapter:
2026-2570 SB2057 CDl SMA.docx 2
